---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="DunningLite — Stripe Failed Payment Recovery for Indie Hackers" description="Automatically recover failed Stripe payments with smart retry schedules and friendly reminder emails. $29 one-time. 5-minute setup. No monthly fees.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="badge">Built for indie founders making $1K–$10K MRR</span>
      <h1 class="hero-title">Stop losing money to <span class="accent">failed payments</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">
        DunningLite monitors your Stripe, retries failed payments on a smart schedule,
        and sends friendly reminder emails — automatically. Recover 30–70% of failed payments.
        $29 one-time, not $100/month.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="#pricing" class="btn-primary">Get DunningLite — $29</a>
        <a href="#how-it-works" class="btn-secondary">See how it works</a>
      </div>
      <p class="hero-note">One-time payment. No subscription. No surprise charges.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pain Points -->
  <section class="pain-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Sound familiar?</h2>
      <div class="pain-grid">
        <div class="pain-card">
          <span class="pain-icon">&#x1f4b8;</span>
          <h3>"I keep losing customers whose cards just expired"</h3>
          <p>Card declines happen constantly — expired cards, bank blocks, temporary holds. Most of these customers want to keep paying you. They just need a nudge at the right time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pain-card">
          <span class="pain-icon">&#x1f9e0;</span>
          <h3>"Stripe's Smart Retries aren't enough"</h3>
          <p>Stripe retries automatically, but you can't customize the schedule, you can't send branded reminder emails, and you have zero visibility into what's happening.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pain-card">
          <span class="pain-icon">&#x1f4b0;</span>
          <h3>"ChurnBuster costs more than some of my customers pay me"</h3>
          <p>ChurnBuster, Stunning, Baremetrics Recover — they all start at $100+/month. When you're doing $2K MRR, spending 5% of revenue on dunning software feels wrong.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How It Works -->
  <section id="how-it-works" class="how-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Set it up in 5 minutes</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">No engineers needed. Seriously.</p>
      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">1</span>
          <h3>Connect your Stripe webhook</h3>
          <p>Add your Stripe webhook URL in the settings. DunningLite listens for <code>invoice.payment_failed</code> events and starts tracking immediately.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">2</span>
          <h3>Smart retries kick in automatically</h3>
          <p>When a payment fails, DunningLite queues retries at +1 day, +3 days, and +7 days — timed to maximize recovery without annoying your customers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">3</span>
          <h3>Friendly emails go out at the right time</h3>
          <p>Your customers get a polite, branded reminder email before each retry. No "YOUR PAYMENT FAILED" panic messages. Just a friendly heads-up that actually gets cards updated.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Features -->
  <section class="features-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Everything you need. Nothing you don't.</h2>
      <div class="features-grid">
        <div class="feature-card">
          <span class="feature-icon">&#x26a1;</span>
          <h3>Stripe Webhook Integration</h3>
          <p>Instant detection of <code>invoice.payment_failed</code> and subscription status changes. Works with all Stripe subscription plans.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <span class="feature-icon">&#x1f504;</span>
          <h3>Smart Retry Schedule</h3>
          <p>+1 day, +3 days, +7 days — the schedule proven to maximize recovery while minimizing customer frustration. Pro users can customize intervals.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <span class="feature-icon">&#x2709;&#xfe0f;</span>
          <h3>Friendly Reminder Emails</h3>
          <p>3 pre-written email templates via Resend that don't sound like debt collectors. Pro users can fully customize with their brand voice.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <span class="feature-icon">&#x1f4ca;</span>
          <h3>Recovery Dashboard</h3>
          <p>See exactly which payments are in recovery, how many retries have happened, and how much revenue you've recovered. No more guessing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <span class="feature-icon">&#x1f514;</span>
          <h3>Owner Notifications</h3>
          <p>Get notified when a payment is recovered. Those are good emails to receive. You're welcome.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <span class="feature-icon">&#x1f680;</span>
          <h3>Deploy in 5 Minutes</h3>
          <p>Next.js + Vercel + Supabase. One <code>vercel deploy</code> and you're live. Vercel Cron runs the retry job automatically every hour.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section id="pricing" class="pricing-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Simple pricing. One-time payment.</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Pay once, use forever. No monthly fees eating into your MRR.</p>
      <div class="pricing-grid">
        <div class="price-card">
          <h3>Free</h3>
          <div class="price">$0</div>
          <p class="price-desc">forever</p>
          <ul class="price-features">
            <li>1 Stripe account</li>
            <li>10 failed payments / month</li>
            <li>Fixed retry schedule (1/3/7 days)</li>
            <li>3 pre-built email templates</li>
            <li>Recovery dashboard</li>
          </ul>
          <a href="/auth/signup" class="btn-secondary btn-block">Get Started Free</a>
        </div>
        <div class="price-card featured">
          <span class="price-badge">Best Value</span>
          <h3>Pro</h3>
          <div class="price">$29</div>
          <p class="price-desc">one-time payment — yours forever</p>
          <ul class="price-features">
            <li>Everything in Free</li>
            <li>Unlimited Stripe accounts</li>
            <li>Unlimited failed payments</li>
            <li>Custom branded email templates</li>
            <li>Customizable retry intervals</li>
            <li>Slack notifications</li>
            <li>Weekly digest report</li>
            <li>CSV export</li>
          </ul>
          <a href="https://dunninglite.vercel.app/pricing" class="btn-primary btn-block">Get Pro for $29</a>
          <p class="price-comparison">vs. ChurnBuster at $100+/month</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="pricing-note">14-day money-back guarantee. If it doesn't work for you, I'll refund you — no questions asked.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">FAQ</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Doesn't Stripe already retry failed payments?</summary>
          <p>It does, but Stripe's Smart Retries are a black box — you can't customize the schedule, you can't send reminder emails to your customers, and you can't see what's happening. DunningLite adds the branded email layer and full visibility that Stripe doesn't give you.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How is this different from ChurnBuster or Stunning?</summary>
          <p>Those are great products — but they're built for funded startups and charge $100–$400/month. If you're doing $2K MRR, paying $100/month for dunning software is 5% of your revenue. DunningLite is $29 one-time. That's it.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How do I actually deploy this?</summary>
          <p>Clone the repo, fill in a <code>.env.local</code> file (Supabase, Stripe, Resend), run the Supabase migration, and do <code>vercel deploy</code>. Then add your webhook URL in Stripe. The whole thing takes about 5 minutes if you've done Vercel deploys before.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What tech stack does this use?</summary>
          <p>Next.js 14, Tailwind CSS, Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth), Stripe SDK, Resend for email, and Vercel Cron for the hourly retry job. Standard indie hacker stack — nothing exotic, nothing to maintain.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What if I want a refund?</summary>
          <p>14-day money-back guarantee. Email me, I'll refund you. No hoops to jump through.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom CTA -->
  <section class="bottom-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Stop leaving money on the table.</h2>
      <p>Failed payments are recoverable revenue. Set up DunningLite once and let it run.</p>
      <a href="#pricing" class="btn-primary">Get DunningLite — $29 one-time</a>
      <p class="cta-note">Or start free — no credit card needed.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer class="tool-footer">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="footer-links">
        <a href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub (coming soon)</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/fixitdev/dunninglite/issues/new?template=bug_report.md&labels=bug" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Report a Bug</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/fixitdev/dunninglite/issues/new?template=feature_request.md&labels=enhancement" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Request a Feature</a>
      </div>
      <p class="footer-credit">Made with &#x2764;&#xfe0f; by <a href="https://fixitdev.com">FixItDev</a></p>
    </div>
  </footer>

</Base>

<style>
  /* Hero */
  .hero {
    padding: 5rem 0 4rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .badge {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--color-border);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    padding: 0.3rem 0.8rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .hero-title {
    font-size: 2.75rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .accent { color: var(--color-accent); }
  .hero-subtitle {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    max-width: 580px;
    margin: 0 auto 2rem;
  }
  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .hero-note {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }

  /* Buttons */
  .btn-primary {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: background 0.2s;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .btn-primary:hover { background: var(--color-accent-hover); text-decoration: none; }
  .btn-secondary {
    display: inline-block;
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--color-text);
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 600;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .btn-secondary:hover { border-color: var(--color-text-muted); text-decoration: none; }
  .btn-block { display: block; text-align: center; width: 100%; }

  /* Sections */
  .section-title {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .section-desc {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  /* Pain Points */
  .pain-section { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .pain-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  .pain-card {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  .pain-icon { font-size: 1.5rem; display: block; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .pain-card h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .pain-card p { color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; }

  /* How It Works */
  .how-section { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .steps {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  .step { text-align: center; }
  .step-num {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .step h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .step p { color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .step code {
    background: var(--color-border);
    padding: 0.1em 0.4em;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.85em;
  }

  /* Features */
  .features-section { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .features-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  .feature-card {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  .feature-icon { font-size: 1.5rem; display: block; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .feature-card h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .feature-card p { color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .feature-card code {
    background: var(--color-border);
    padding: 0.1em 0.4em;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.85em;
  }

  /* Pricing */
  .pricing-section {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .pricing-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
    text-align: left;
  }
  .price-card {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 2rem;
    position: relative;
  }
  .price-card.featured { border-color: var(--color-accent); }
  .price-badge {
    position: absolute;
    top: -10px;
    right: 1rem;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .price-card h3 { font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .price {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
  }
  .price-desc {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .price-features {
    list-style: none;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .price-features li {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    padding: 0.3rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }
  .price-features li::before {
    content: "\2713";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-success);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .price-comparison {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    opacity: 0.7;
  }
  .pricing-note {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  /* FAQ */
  .faq-section { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .faq-list {
    max-width: 700px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  .faq-item {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .faq-item summary {
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    background: var(--color-surface);
  }
  .faq-item summary:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }
  .faq-item p {
    padding: 0 1.25rem 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  .faq-item code {
    background: var(--color-border);
    padding: 0.1em 0.4em;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.85em;
  }

  /* Bottom CTA */
  .bottom-cta {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .bottom-cta h2 { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .bottom-cta p { color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .cta-note {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  /* Footer */
  .tool-footer {
    padding: 2rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .footer-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .footer-links a {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .footer-links a:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }
  .footer-credit {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
  .footer-credit a { color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration: none; }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hero-title { font-size: 1.75rem; }
    .hero-subtitle { font-size: 1rem; }
    .section-title { font-size: 1.35rem; }
    .price { font-size: 2rem; }
  }
</style>
